            <biogHist>
                <p>Donald MacRae was born to Duncan MacRae, crofter, and Chirsty n√©e MacRae. He was
                    recorded in 1851 at Borve on Barra staying with the lighthouse keeper, Joseph
                    Thomson, and his family. Donald classed himself as a tailor. Ten years later he
                    was farming 30 acres of land at Buaile nam Bodach. Staying with him was his
                    mother, who was now 60, his brother Farquhar, aged 33, a ploughman, and his
                    three sisters, Margaret (35), a dressmaker, Mary (31), a domestic servant, and
                    Ann (29), also a domestic servant. they lived in a house with at least three
                    rooms with windows. </p>
                <p>In 1871 Donald was staying with Duncan Sinclair and his family on Berneray. In
                    1881 he had become the sub-postmaster at Buaile nam Bodach, with his brother and
                    sisters living with him. He also had plasterer Donald Silver from Duirinish and
                    a joiner from Tiree, whcih would suggest that work was being done to the
                    postmasters house. </p>
                <p>In February 1891, Donald died from unknown causes. His brother signed the death
                    certificate. He died unmarried.</p>
